.TH "mlx4_ACCESS_REG" 9 "mlx4_ACCESS_REG" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mlx4_ACCESS_REG \- Generic access reg command.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mlx4_ACCESS_REG
.BI "(struct mlx4_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u16 reg_id "  ","
.BI "enum mlx4_access_reg_method method "  ","
.BI "u16 reg_len "  ","
.BI "void *reg_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
mlx4_dev.
.IP "reg_id" 12
register ID to access.
.IP "method" 12
Access method Read/Write.
.IP "reg_len" 12
register length to Read/Write in bytes.
.IP "reg_data" 12
reg_data pointer to Read/Write From/To.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Access ConnectX registers FW command.
Returns 0 on success and copies outbox mlx4_access_reg data
field into reg_data or a negative error code.
